    "body": "@axic At the moment I think this *is* supported for npm installed solc - the relevant code is [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/next/packages/truffle-compile/compilerSupplier.js#L142-L154). It pulls `solc` in via a `require` modified to be web-packable. Does this work for your case? \r\n\r\nUsage:\r\n```javascript\r\ncompilers: {\r\n  solc: {\r\n    version: \"/Users/user/.nvm/versions/node/v8.9.4/lib/node_modules/solc\"    \r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
